 A footnote: Since there was to be no grade inflation in the down clue, I suppose that's why entering the double rebus is technically incorrect - because it puts the inflation in both the Across and Down. Entering the single letter puts the inflation in the Across and not in the Down.
E.g., High Five is written as High Dive, inflating F to D. But Add is written as Add - no inflation. If you enter F/D, there would be inflation in both Across and Down.

